ID001: Inconsistent typography for "Switch Profile" on Settings screen

Title
Settings: "Switch Profile" typography is inconsistent with surrounding UI

Description
On the Settings screen, the "Switch Profile" text under the default user profile uses a different font style/weight compared to the rest of the application.

This creates an inconsistent visual appearance and makes the profile section look different from other settings.

### Steps to Reproduce
1. Open Settings.
2. Navigate to the profile section at the top.
3. Observe the "Switch Profile" text.

### Expected Behavior
The "Switch Profile" text should use the same typography (font family, weight, size, and spacing) as the rest of the application.

### Actual Behavior
The typography appears different and visually inconsistent with the rest of the Settings screen.

### Priority
Medium

### Category
UI / Design

ID002: Search bar action icons should be aligned horizontally

Title
All Words: Search bar action icons are stacked vertically instead of being aligned in a single row

Description
On the All Words screen, the action icons (Clear, Delete/Trash, and Recent Searches) displayed beside the sentence/search field are arranged vertically.

This occupies unnecessary vertical space and differs from the horizontal layout used for the search bar below.

### Steps to Reproduce
1. Open the All Words screen.
2. Observe the action icons beside the sentence/search field.

### Expected Behavior
The Clear (X), Delete/Trash, and Recent Search icons should be placed in a single horizontal row similar to the search field controls.

### Actual Behavior
The icons are stacked vertically, making the interface less compact and less visually consistent.

### Priority
Medium

### Category
UI / UX

ID002: Improve consistency between search field and action controls

Title
All Words: Action controls should follow the same layout pattern as the search bar

Description
The search field uses a clean horizontal layout, while the action controls (Clear, Delete, Recent) use a separate vertical floating layout.

Using a consistent horizontal arrangement would improve usability and visual consistency.

### Expected Behavior
Action controls should follow the same design pattern as the search bar, with icons aligned horizontally and evenly spaced.

### Benefit
- Better visual consistency
- Easier reachability
- Reduced visual clutter
- Improved accessibility

### Priority
Low

### Category
UI / UX Enhancement
